flowRoot.flowPara: Suitable for both audio and control voltages, with bonus features that don't compromise the minimalist philosophy: positive and negative offset; simultaneous DC- and AC-coupled outputs; maximum gain a little over unity for when you need that extra push over the cliff. It can also function as a transistor distortion effect, by offsetting the signal until it clips and then using the AC-coupled output.

Turn all knobs fully counterclockwise. Apply powerto the module with nothing plugged into the input,and measure the DC voltage of the DC-coupled out-put. Adjust R7 at the top of the board, labelledoffset null, to bring the output as close to 0V asis reasonably possible. It is unlikely that you will beable to get it to stay at exactly zero.
